# Code Standards

This project follows specific code quality standards defined in [pyproject.toml](mdc:pyproject.toml):

## Type Checking

- Uses mypy with strict type checking
- All functions must have type annotations
- Configuration is in the `[tool.mypy]` section of [pyproject.toml](mdc:pyproject.toml)

## Code Style and Linting

- Uses ruff for linting and formatting
- Target Python version is 3.9+
- Line length is 120 characters
- Configuration is in the `[tool.ruff]` section of [pyproject.toml](mdc:pyproject.toml)
- Enforced by pre-commit hooks in [.pre-commit-config.yaml](mdc:.pre-commit-config.yaml)

## Testing Standards

- All code should have test coverage
- Tests are located in [tests](mdc:tests)
- Coverage settings in `[tool.coverage]` section of [pyproject.toml](mdc:pyproject.toml)

## Documentation

- All public functions/classes must have docstrings
- Documentation follows style in [src/rags/foo.py](mdc:src/rags/foo.py)
- Documentation is built with MkDocs as configured in [mkdocs.yml](mdc:mkdocs.yml)
